Sentencas: Transition metal elements were employed to customize the standard Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6 (SFM) material, with the goal of improving the performance of the SFM cathode in protonconducting solid oxide fuel cells (H-SOFCs).
Titulo: New Sr2FeMo0.5X0.5O6 (X1/4Ni, Co, Mn, Zn) cathodes for proton-conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: Sr2FeMo0.5X0.5O6 (X = Ni, Co, Mn, Zn) materials were prepared, but it was discovered that only the dopants Ni and Co can form a pure phase, whereas the dopants Mn and Zn produced an obvious secondary phase.
Titulo: New Sr2FeMo0.5X0.5O6 (X1/4Ni, Co, Mn, Zn) cathodes for proton-conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: When comparing oxygen vacancies and oxygen diffusion kinetics, utilizing the Co-dopant exhibited clear advantages.
Titulo: New Sr2FeMo0.5X0.5O6 (X1/4Ni, Co, Mn, Zn) cathodes for proton-conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: The Co-doped SFM had a higher oxygen vacancy content and faster oxygen diffusion kinetics than both the standard and Ni-doped SFM cathodes.
Titulo: New Sr2FeMo0.5X0.5O6 (X1/4Ni, Co, Mn, Zn) cathodes for proton-conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: The energy barrier for the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) at the Co-doped SFM cathode was 0.76 eV, which was much lower than that for the SFM and Ni-doped SFM, which were 5.52 and 2.28 eV, respectively.
Titulo: New Sr2FeMo0.5X0.5O6 (X1/4Ni, Co, Mn, Zn) cathodes for proton-conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: As a result, the Co-doped SFM's cathode reaction was greatly accelerated, resulting in a high fuel cell performance of 1306 mW cm-2 at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: New Sr2FeMo0.5X0.5O6 (X1/4Ni, Co, Mn, Zn) cathodes for proton-conducting SOFCs

Sentencas: This finding suggests that using the appropriate dopant can alleviate the low-performance problem of the traditional SFM cathode, resulting in a promising cathode option for H-SOFCs.
Titulo: New Sr2FeMo0.5X0.5O6 (X1/4Ni, Co, Mn, Zn) cathodes for proton-conducting SOFCs
